[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1m)[0m [1m([0mBuildId:                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m:[1;92m703:3[0m in Stream_Read                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow is reported during the processing of a     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         client “conference create” request in FreeRDP. An [1;36m8[0m-byte write performed by         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Stream_Read exceeds the bounds of a heap buffer by exactly [1;36m8[0m bytes. The overflow is [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         detected in winpr/stream.h when parsing client network data via core/gcc.c          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         routines, after a buffer of [1;36m992[0m bytes was allocated by mcs_new in core/mcs.c.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue type                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - Heap-based buffer overflow [1m([0m[1;36m8[0m-byte write past the end of a heap-allocated       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         region[1m)[0m.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - What happens                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - A [1;36m992[0m-byte buffer is allocated via calloc in mcs_new [1m([0mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.c[1m)[0m.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - Stream_Read [1m([0mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h:[1;36m703[0m[1m)[0m attempts to write [1;36m8[0m bytes        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         starting exactly at offset [1;36m992[0m, overrunning the buffer.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - This write occurs during gcc_read_client_network_data                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mlibfreerdp/core/gcc.[1;92mc:1875[0m[1m)[0m, which is part of the sequence:                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • gcc_read_client_network_data → gcc_read_client_data_blocks →                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         gcc_read_conference_create_request → mcs_recv_connect_initial →                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request → test_server harness.                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - The overflow is reliably triggered under fuzzing via TestFuzzCoreServer         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mcore/test/TestFuzzCoreServer.c[1m)[0m.                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - AddressSanitizer labels the severity as “SCARINESS: [1;36m42[0m.”                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - The write target [1m([0m[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[1m)[0m is exactly [1;36m0[0m bytes past the end of the        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         allocated [1;36m992[0m-byte region [1m([0m[1;36m0x519000001980[0m–[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[1m)[0m.                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code areas for investigation                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. Stream_Read implementation in winpr/include/winpr/stream.h around line [1;36m703[0m:    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         verify bounds checks for multi-byte reads.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. GCC parsing functions in libfreerdp/core/gcc.c, especially at lines:           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - gcc_read_client_network_data [1m([0m[1;36m1875[0m[1m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - gcc_read_client_data_blocks [1m([0m[1;36m617[0m[1m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - gcc_read_conference_create_request [1m([0m[1;36m414[0m[1m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. The allocation logic in mcs_new [1m([0mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.[1;92mc:1446[0m[1m)[0m: confirm buffer   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sizing matches expected reading operations.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. The validation entry point freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mlibfreerdp/core/freerdp.[1;92mc:1438[0m–[1;36m1441[0m[1m)[0m.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m5[0m. The fuzzing harness in core/test/TestFuzzCoreServer.c, to understand how input [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         shapes the faulty code paths.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconst*, unsigned long[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerDriver.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m862:9[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x55d530c0e0b2[0m[39m in main [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerMain.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m20:10[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x7fa63487f082[0m[39m in __libc_start_main [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuildId: [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m5792732f783158c66fb4f3756458ca24e46e827d[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m703:3[0m[39m in Stream_Read[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_snippets>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.h:[0m[1;36m147[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m149[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:    [0m[39mINT8 channelCount;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    [0m[39mrdpMcsChannel* channels;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Update the rdpMcs struct to use an unsigned type for channelCount[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In libfreerdp/core/mcs.h, change the declaration of channelCount from INT8 to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUINT8.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Rationale: the stream parser uses Stream_Read_UINT8 to populate channelCount. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeeping channelCount signed leads to negative values [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhen the incoming byte >[0m[1;36m127[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich in turn get miscast as large unsigned loop bounds and drive out-of-bounds [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccesses.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add bounds-checking immediately after reading channelCount in the GCC parsing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In libfreerdp/core/gcc.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39min gcc_read_conference_create_request, around the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_Read_UINT8 call[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. After `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` insert:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs->channelCount > mcs->channelCountMax[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return FALSE;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        where `mcs->channelCountMax` is the number of channel slots allocated in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmcs_new [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtypically defined by a constant like MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS or stored in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrdpMcs instance[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. If no channelCountMax field exists, use the compile-time constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to cap incoming channelCount.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents any loop that iterates over channels [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwalking off the end of the pre-allocated channels array and avoids writing beyond [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Audit all loops driven by channelCount in the MCS receive/parse code[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Anywhere channelCount is used to iterate over `mcs->channels[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` or to read [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional channel descriptors, ensure the iteration stops at the validated [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannelCount [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow an unsigned, bounds-checked value[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code paths should write into the channels array past its allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality and fuzz harness[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We are not touching any harness or test code; the same TestFuzzCoreServer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point will exercise the code, but oversized or negative channelCount values [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now be caught and cause a clean parse-failure instead of heap overflow.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing unit tests and RDP protocol flows for valid inputs remain [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged since channelCount only ever assumed to be in a valid range.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Regression Testing[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run AddressSanitizer on the fuzz harness to confirm the specific [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite past the buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mStream_Read at offset [0m[1;36m992[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m no longer occurs.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full FreeRDP test suite to ensure there are no unintended [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mside-effects.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changing channelCount to UINT8 aligns the variable type with the data read [0m[1;39m([0m[39man [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned byte[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and eliminates the negative‐value loophole that underpinned the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Immediate bounds checking enforces that the client cannot specify more channels [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan we allocated in mcs_new.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We do not alter any external libraries, harness, or test code. All changes are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocalized to the core parsing and data‐structure definitions.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach follows existing patterns in FreeRDP where counts read from the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwire are validated against compile-time limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., the number of MCS channels, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morder of pdu identifiers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before loops that consume memory.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side Effects & Mitigations:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If any downstream logic assumed channelCount could be negative [0m[1;39m([0m[39munlikely in valid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRDP flows[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, changing to UINT8 might slightly alter error-path handling. But with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproper bounds checks, erroneous inputs now fail early and cleanly.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensure that the constant used for maximum channels matches the capacity allocated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min mcs_new; mismatches would either reject valid clients [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif too low[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or re‐open [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif too high[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This constant is already used in mcs_new and should be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreferenced directly.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerDriver.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m862:9[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x55d530c0e0b2[0m[39m in main [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerMain.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m20:10[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x7fa63487f082[0m[39m in __libc_start_main [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuildId: [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m5792732f783158c66fb4f3756458ca24e46e827d[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m703:3[0m[39m in Stream_Read[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe FreeRDP codebase triggers an AddressSanitizer heap‐buffer overflow when reading[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclient network data in `gcc_read_client_network_data` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `Stream_Read`. The overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs because a buffer of [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m bytes is read past its end by an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte write in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Stream_Read`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch attempt was made to:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change the type of `channelCount` in `rdp_mcs` from `INT8` to `UINT8`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add additional `Stream_Read_UINT8` calls and bounds checks for `channelCount` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma new `initiator` field in `gcc_read_conference_create_request`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApplying that patch produced several compilation errors:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. “expression is not assignable” at the `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` line.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. “use of undeclared identifier ‘MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS’”.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. “no member named ‘initiator’ in ‘struct rdp_mcs’”.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a heap‐buffer overflow in `Stream_Read` when [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data` calls into `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meventually `gcc_read_conference_create_request`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is a WRITE of [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes just past a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m‐byte region allocated via [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`calloc` in `mcs_new`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack shows the fuzzer’s `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → `test_server` → [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request` → `mcs_recv_connect_initial` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_conference_create_request` → `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` → [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data` → `Stream_Read`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocated buffer covers offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m1980[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…1d60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The write occurs at [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x[0m[39m…1d60, exactly one byte past the end.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error originates in reading client data blocks; the code does not validate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe number or size of channels before reading fields into the `mcs` structure.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The root structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rdp_mcs`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has a `channelCount` field of type `INT8` and a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer to `channels`, suggesting channel parsing logic may be under‐validating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `libfreerdp/core/mcs.h`, change  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   `INT8 channelCount;`  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   to  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   `UINT8 channelCount;`  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `libfreerdp/core/gcc.c`, after  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mgcc_read_client_data_blocks[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, mcs, length[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   insert:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs->channelCount > MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->initiator[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   and then `return TRUE;`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation error “expression is not assignable” at `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`. The `Stream_Read_UINT8` macro expands to an assignment [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpression, not a statement, so it cannot take an lvalue address parameter as used.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS` is not defined or included in scope in `gcc.c`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The struct `rdp_mcs` does not have a member named `initiator`, so [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`&mcs->initiator` is invalid.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definition of `Stream_Read_UINT8` and other stream‐reading macros in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`winpr/stream.h`, to understand their correct usage and expected parameters.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `rdp_mcs` struct in `mcs.h` to confirm which fields exist, their sizes, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended semantics [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`channelCount`, any `initiator` field, and how channels are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstored[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The constants or limits for channel counts [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS` or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and where they are declared.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic in `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` and [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_conference_create_request` for how many bytes are read versus how much [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas allocated, and whether length parameters are consistently checked prior to each[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m=================================================================[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address [0m[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[39m at pc[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x55d531099d91[0m[39m bp [0m[1;36m0x7ffc37862350[0m[39m sp [0m[1;36m0x7ffc37862348[0m                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1863[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1864[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.h:[0m[1;36m143[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m149[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:    [0m[39mBOOL userChannelJoined;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:    [0m[39mBOOL globalChannelJoined;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:    [0m[39mBOOL messageChannelJoined;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:    [0m[39mINT8 channelCount;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    [0m[39mrdpMcsChannel* channels;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.[0m[1;92mc:1443[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1449[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1443[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mmcs_init_domain_parameters[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&mcs->domainParameters, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0xFFFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1444[0m[39m:   [0m[39mmcs->channelCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1445[0m[39m:   [0m[39mmcs->baseChannelId = MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNEL_ID + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1446[0m[39m:   [0m[39mmcs->channels = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrdpMcsChannel*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCHANNEL_MAX_COUNT, [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrdpMcsChannel[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1447[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1448[0m[39m:   [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!mcs->channels[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1449[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39mgoto out_free;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h:[0m[1;36m614[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m619[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m614[0m[39m:#define [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s, _v[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m      \[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m615[0m[39m:    [0m[39mdo                                 \[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m616[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m                                  \[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m617[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m_v = [0m[1;35mstream_read_u8[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s, TRUE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; \[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m618[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m619[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Update the `rdp_mcs` struct to use an unsigned [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit count:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libfreerdp/core/mcs.h`, change[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `INT8  channelCount;`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `UINT8 channelCount;`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This aligns on-wire semantics [0m[1;39m([0m[39man unsigned count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with in-memory storage and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents sign-extension or negative-index issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correctly read and validate `channelCount` inside [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data`:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libfreerdp/core/gcc.c`, locate `gcc_read_client_network_data` around the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock‐length checks.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the existing sequence:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* channelCount *[0m[35m/[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockLength < [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmcs->channelCount * [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs->channelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Read the on-wire unsigned channel count *[0m[35m/[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Reject values larger than our allocation *[0m[35m/[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs->channelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure the buffer contains enough bytes for all channel entries *[0m[35m/[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         size_t needed = [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmcs->channelCount * [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockLength < needed[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rationale:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m We now use the unsigned `UINT8` field directly with `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno `&` needed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Early bounds check prevents an attacker from specifying a huge [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`channelCount` that would cause multiplication overflow or allow out-of-bounds [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Only after verifying `channelCount` ≤ `CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT` do we compute [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`needed = [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m + channelCount×[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m` and check `blockLength`, avoiding wrap-around safety[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhazards.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Remove the erroneous additions in `gcc_read_conference_create_request`:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Revert the last patch’s insertion of[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs->channelCount > MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return FALSE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->initiator[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     because:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `Stream_Read_UINT8` should not be called with `&mcs->channelCount`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `MCS_GLOBAL_CHANNELS` is undefined; the correct cap is `CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `rdp_mcs` has no `initiator` member—reading that belongs to GCC layers, not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe MCS struct.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Ensure all necessary headers are included:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify `gcc.c` includes `core/mcs.h` so that `CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT` and the new [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UINT8 channelCount` are in scope.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Regression considerations:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch does not touch the harness or fuzzing logic. All existing tests and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musage of `channelCount` remain intact, aside from its widened unsigned range.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception catches are introduced; we only add a narrow bounds check. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ABI change from `INT8` to `UINT8` affects only internal struct semantics; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallers always treated it as an unsigned count.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach zeroes in on the root cause [0m[1;39m([0m[39munchecked or mis‐typed `channelCount`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than misplacing reads in higher-level functions.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It preserves existing logic: channels are still read in [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data`, just with proper validation first.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It eliminates the heap‐buffer‐overflow by preventing any `channelCount > [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCHANNEL_MAX_COUNT` from driving the loop that writes past the allocated `channels` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar patterns in this codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in `gcc_read_client_security_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready validate block sizes after reading counts; we mirror that style.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo external libraries, harness code, or test code are modified, so existing [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality and tests should continue to pass unaltered.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
